18/12/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey and Syria signed a memorandum of understanding on security co-operation Wednesday (17 December).
Syrian Interior Minster Ali Hammud said the agreement means that Syrian authorities would capture anyone whom Turkey views as a security threat.
Meanwhile, Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul continued his official visit to Japan, meeting with counterpart Yoriko Kawaguchi on Wednesday.
The two officials discussed possible co-operation on reconstruction projects in Iraq, bilateral relations and international efforts to fight terrorism.
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 17/12/03)
